name: LemmyClient
desc: A client that interacts with a Lemmy instance. The client must be initialized before it can be used.

name: account
desc: Interface to work with AccountHelper instances.

name: accountInformation
desc: The account information. This is fetched when the client is initialized if the auth parameter is passed in.

name: auth
desc:
The authentication token for the current client instance.
This is used to authenticate requests to the Lemmy instance as a given user.

name: feed
desc: Interface to work with FeedHelper instances.

name: get
desc: Helper method to perform GET requests.

name: httpClient
desc: The HTTP client to use when interacting with the Lemmy instance.

name: initialize
desc: Initializes the client with the given parameters.

name: instance
desc: The URL of the Lemmy instance, excluding the scheme.

name: post
desc: Helper method to perform POST requests.

name: scheme
desc: The scheme to use when interacting with the Lemmy instance. Defaults to 'https'.

name: site
desc: Interface to work with SiteHelper instances.

name: siteInformation
desc: The site information. This is fetched when the client is initialized.

name: user
desc: Interface to work with UserHelper instances.

name: version
desc: The version of the Lemmy API to use. Defaults to 'v4'.
